        "id": "97876",
        "type": "nodetool.workflows.base_node.Comment",
        "data": {
          "comment": "# ✨ Image Enhance — a live photo editor\n\nFive GPU filters in a row: **Denoise → Brightness/Contrast → Saturation → Sharpen**. Each filter exposes plain numeric properties (amount, radius, contrast…), so the mini app binds one slider to each and the preview re-renders as you drag.\n\n**Why it's a graph, not a prompt:** the whole chain runs on the GPU in the browser. No LLM, no API key, no per-run cost — which is what makes real-time slider feedback possible. Reorder the filters, add a Vignette or Hue shift, and the app picks up the new controls automatically.\n\n**Defaults** give a gentle all-round lift; push Sharpen and Contrast for punch, or raise Denoise to clean up a noisy phone shot before sharpening."
        },
